#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:18
msgid "Scope"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:20
msgid ""
"This policy applies to all products offered by Mattermost, including web "
"applications, software, digital content, and related services that may be"
" used by individuals with disabilities. The policy applies to both "
"internal and external stakeholders, including potential customers, "
"partners, and government agencies seeking accessibility information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:23
msgid "VPAT creation process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:25
msgid ""
"**Initial Assessment**: Each product is reviewed for accessibility "
"compliance based on the relevant standards. This assessment is conducted "
"by trained accessibility personnel or certified third-party auditors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:27
msgid ""
"**VPAT Documentation**: A VPAT is created based on the findings from the "
"initial assessment. This document details each accessibility criterion "
"and the level of conformance achieved, along with explanations for any "
"known gaps or alternative solutions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:29
msgid ""
"**Review and Approval**: VPATs are reviewed by our accessibility "
"compliance team to ensure accuracy, completeness, and consistency. Any "
"areas not in full compliance are documented with explanations and, where "
"possible, a roadmap for future improvements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:31
msgid ""
"**Publishing and Distribution**: Once approved, VPATs are made available "
"upon request for customers, partners, and other stakeholders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:33
msgid ""
"Accessibility standards and regulations evolve, and our products and "
"services continue to improve. VPATs will be reviewed and updated on a "
"regular basis, at minimum annually, to reflect the current state of our "
"accessibility compliance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:36
msgid "Roles and responsibilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:38
msgid ""
"**Product Accessibility Team**: Conducts assessments, documents "
"accessibility features, and prepares VPATs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:39
msgid ""
"**Legal and Compliance Team**: Reviews VPATs to ensure legal requirements"
" are met and accessibility claims are accurate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:40
msgid ""
"**Customer Support Team**: Handles requests for VPATs and assists "
"customers with accessibility questions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:43
msgid "Customer and partner requests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:45
msgid ""
"Customers and partners may request access to specific VPATs or additional"
" accessibility information. The organization is committed to providing "
"accurate and timely responses and will work to accommodate requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/accessibility-compliance-policy.rst:47
msgid ""
"To request a VPAT document, contact us at `accessibility@mattermost.com "
"<mailto:accessibility@mattermost.com>`_."
msgstr ""

